### Task Tracker API - REST Client

@baseUrl = https://tasktracker-4pc3.onrender.com
@contentType = application/json

### 1. GET all tasks
GET {{baseUrl}}/tasks


### 2. CREATE a new task
POST {{baseUrl}}/tasks
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Buy groceries",
  "description": "Milk, eggs, bread",
  "priority": "medium"
}


### 3. CREATE another task (for testing)
POST {{baseUrl}}/tasks
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Finish project",
  "description": "Complete the task tracker UI",
  "priority": "high"
}


### 4. GET a specific task (change id to test)
GET {{baseUrl}}/tasks/1


### 5. UPDATE a task (change id and fields as needed)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tasks/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Buy groceries",
  "description": "Milk, eggs, bread, cheese",
  "priority": "high",
  "completed": false
}


### 6. MARK task as completed
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tasks/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Buy groceries",
  "description": "Milk, eggs, bread, cheese",
  "priority": "high",
  "completed": true
}


### 7. DELETE a task (change id as needed)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/tasks/1
